Description: Ring foot and floor sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery plate or shallow bowl; glazed mostly misfired orange-brown; glazed save for stand-ring; on floor: two bands of impressed small palmettes on double-tongue band; inscription cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 539)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1915)
